# Next.js App Router Architecture

- Default to Server Components; add `"use client"` only for interactivity, browser APIs, or local UI state.
- Keep data fetching and secure logic on the server boundary whenever possible.
- Use Server Actions or route handlers for writes and privileged operations.
- Keep page-level files thin: compose from focused feature components and shared UI blocks.
- Preserve a clear user flow:
  - unauthenticated -> landing/auth
  - new user -> onboarding
  - returning user -> dashboard
- For async UX, provide loading states and resilient error boundaries for critical paths.
